g xggy1nq x1a2a7pz _a6hd" href="https://www.instagram.com/objectivecancer/p/DCInioAxL9m/" role="link" tabindex="0"><div class="_aagu"><div class="_aagv" style="padding-bottom: 133.333%;"><img alt="Get to know the future of genetic editing: CRISPR! This groundbreaking tool is revolutionizing medicine, and we’re excited to dive into its potential for fighting diseases, including cancer. A huge shoutout to Beatrix Shippy, one of our amazing Objective: Cancer members at our Boston Latin Academy chapter, for creating our very first post on the latest in science and health! Follow along as we explore the science behind genetic advancements and how they bring us closer to a cancer-free future. 💪🔬 

Do you want to make a post just like this? Go to our linktree in our bio and press “Outreach Initiative.” Students, you can earn up to 2 hours for each post you make. It’s a great way to boost up your hours, while also doing research to raise cancer awareness. 👩‍🔬

