pz _a6hd" href="https://www.instagram.com/objectivecancer/p/C8z4EWsAbTO/" role="link" tabindex="0"><div class="_aagu"><div class="_aagv" style="padding-bottom: 133.333%;"><img alt="Today, we are talking about …🥁🥁… Lung Cancer! Topics we have covered: what is lung cancer, its different types, causes, classification by grade, treatment options, and available support resources. Did you know that lung cancer, despite being the leading cause of cancer-related deaths globally, is highly preventable? Since smoking is responsible for approximately 85% of all lung cancer cases, quitting smoking can significantly reduce the risk. 

Stay informed and be proactive about your health. 

