#cancerawareness #cancerresearch #cancer #beatcancer #fightcancer #cancerproject #cancersupport #celebratelife #health #education #stupidcancer #curecancer #objectivecancer #earlydetectionsaveslives #empoweryouhealth" class="x5yr21d xu96u03 x10l6tqk x13vifvy x87ps6o xh8yej3" crossorigin="anonymous" src="./post6_files/443227973_7501453919974518_8906914769637765524_n.jpg" style="object-fit: cover;"></div><div class="_aagw"></div></div><div class="html-div xdj266r x14z9mp xat24cr x1lziwak xexx8yu xyri2b x18d9i69 x1c1uobl x9f619 xjbqb8w x78zum5 x15mokao x1ga7v0g x16uus16 xbiv7yw x1uhb9sk x1plvlek xryxfnj x1c4vz4f x2lah0s xdt5ytf xqjyukv x1qjc9v5 x1oa3qoh x1nhvcw1"><div class="xuk3077 x972fbf x10w94by x1qhh985 x14e42zd x1ey2m1c x9f619 x78zum5 xdt5ytf x2lah0s xln7xf2 xk390pu xtijo5x x1o0tod x1nhvcw1 xdj266r x14z9mp xat24cr x1lziwak xexx8yu xyri2b x18d9i69 x1c1uobl x47corl x10l6tqk x13vifvy x11njtxf"><div class="html-div xexx8yu xyri2b x18d9i69 x1c1uobl x9f619 xjbqb8w x78zum5 x15mokao x1ga7v0g x16uus16 xbiv7yw x1xmf6yo x1xegmmw x1e56ztr x13fj5qh x1n2onr6 x1plvlek xryxfnj x1c4vz4f x2lah0s xdt5ytf xqjyukv x1qjc9v5 x1oa3qoh x1nhvcw1"><svg aria-label="Carousel" class="x1lliihq x1n2onr6 x9bdzbf" fill="currentColor" height="20" role="img" viewBox="0 0 48 48" width="20"><title>Carousel</title><path d="M34.8 29.7V11c0-2.9-2.3-5.2-5.2-5.2H11c-2.9 0-5.2 2.3-5.2 5.2v18.7c0 2.9 2.3 5.2 5.2 5.2h18.7c2.8-.1 5.1-2.4 5.1-5.2zM39.2 15v16.1c0 4.5-3.7 8.2-8.2 8.2H14.9c-.6 0-.9.7-.5 1.1 1 1.1 2.4 1.8 4.1 1.8h13.4c5.7 0 10.3-4.6 10.3-10.3V18.5c0-1.6-.7-3.1-1.8-4.1-.5-.4-1.2 0-1.2.6z"></path></svg></div></div></div></a></div><div class="x1lliihq x1n2onr6 xh8yej3 x4gyw5p x14z9mp xhe4ym4 xaudc5v x1j53mea"><a class="x1i10hfl xjbqb8w x1ejq31n x18oe1m7 x1sy0etr xstzfhl x972fbf x10w94by x1qhh985 x14e42zd x9f619 x1ypdohk xt0psk2 x3ct3a4 xdj266r x14z9mp xat24cr x1lziwak xexx8yu xyri2b x18d9i69 x1c1uobl x16tdsg8 x1hl2dhg xggy1nq x1a2a7pz _a6hd" href="https://www.instagram.com/objectivecancer/p/C6se9l2sG0k/" role="link" tabindex="0"><div class="_aagu"><div class="_aagv" style="padding-bottom: 133.333%;"><img alt="Today marks World Ovarian Cancer Day!

What even is ovarian cancer…? Ovarian cancer is a type of cancer that forms in female ovaries. It is usually diagnosed during the later stages which makes it more challenging to treat. Early detection and treatment are crucial for improving outcomes. Reach out to a healthcare professional soon to be safe. 

Studies have shown that not many women know about Ovarian Cancer. According to the American Cancer Society, a women’s risk of Ovarian Cancer is about 1 in 87, and her chances of dying from it is about 1 in 130. Furthermore, the World Ovarian Cancer Coalition has projected that by 2050, the number of women around the world with Ovarian Cancer will rise over 55% leading to 503,448 diagnosed. This shows how women are being left behind in the race for health. The more likely a woman knows about these risks and conditions the more likely she will get herself tested. Reach out to healthcare providers if you can have a diagnostic test, like a Rectovaginal pelvic exam, a transvaginal ultrasound, or a CA-125 blood test if you have any unexplained signs or symptoms of ovarian cancer. It is best to be tested and have it confirmed, rather than not! 

The World Ovarian Cancer Day is a global campaign that raises awareness about Ovarian Cancer and its impact on women’s health worldwide. Supporters around the world aim to reduce the number of deaths in women caused by Ovarian Cancer through increased awareness and action. It first starts with knowing the main symptoms and detecting it early. Gain the knowledge, spread it, and save lives. Raise awareness so that no woman will be left behind!

Objective: Cancer - serves as an educational resource to inform and learn about cancer.

Follow for more! 🎗️
